        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 22 at 4:22PM CDT until July 22 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles southwest of
Rousseau, or 9 miles southeast of Pierre, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Rousseau and Lake Sharpe around 425 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this severe thunderstorm include
Canning.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm is producing large hail. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows.</instruction>
